    management: ["Administer prescribed antibiotics promptly after cultures obtained", "Maintain IV fluids as ordered", "Maintain neutral thermal environment", "Support respiratory function as needed (oxygen, positioning)", "Maintain strict hand hygiene and infection control precautions", "Prepare for possible lumbar puncture if meningitis suspected"],
    nursingActions: ["Monitor vital signs frequently (temperature, HR, RR, BP)", "Assess for subtle signs of sepsis (lethargy, poor feeding, color changes)", "Report temperature instability (hypothermia OR fever) immediately", "Monitor feeding tolerance and report poor feeding", "Maintain strict aseptic technique with all invasive lines", "Document behavioral changes (\"not looking right\" is a valid concern)", "Monitor for apnea and bradycardia episodes"],
