    management: ["Initiate phototherapy as ordered (blue-green light, maximize skin exposure)", "Protect eyes with opaque shields during phototherapy at all times", "Increase feeding frequency to promote bilirubin excretion through stool", "Remove all clothing except diaper during phototherapy", "Monitor for bronze baby syndrome (contraindicated with conjugated hyperbilirubinemia)", "Prepare for exchange transfusion if bilirubin reaches critical levels"],
    nursingActions: ["Assess skin color systematically using blanch technique", "Monitor bilirubin levels and report rising trends to provider", "Ensure eye shields remain properly positioned (check frequently)", "Monitor temperature during phototherapy (risk of overheating)", "Assess hydration status (wet diapers, mucous membranes, fontanelle)", "Increase fluid intake to compensate for insensible losses during phototherapy", "Educate parents on jaundice progression, phototherapy, and when to seek care"],
